<stack-static>
    <statement><div><p>An amusement park is the shape of a regular pentagon. Each side of the park measures <m>{106}\,\text{m}</m> and the height of the pentagon park is <m>{40} \, \text{m}</m>.  Calculate the total area of the park.</p>



<p><m>\text{The area of the park} =</m> <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{m}^2</m></p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><p><alert>Given:</alert><br/>
• Side length = <m>{106}</m> m <br/>
• Height of one triangle (from the center to the midpoint of a side) = <m>{40}</m> m
</p>

<p>
<m>\text{Area of pentagon} = 5 \times \text{area of one triangle}</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Find the area of one triangle</alert></p>

<p>
Each triangle has: <br/>
• Base = side of the pentagon = <m>{106}</m> m <br/>
• Height = <m>{40}</m> m <br/>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Area of one triangle} \amp = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{1}{2} \times {106} \times {40}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {2120}\, \text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p><alert>Find the total area of the pentagon</alert></p>

<p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Total area} \amp = 5 \times \text{area of one triangle}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = 5 \times {2120}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {10600}\, \text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
<m>\text{Therefore, the total area of the pentagon-shaped park is } {10600} \text{ m}^2.</m>
</p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>10600</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>